## Setup Required

> [!CAUTION]
> Because we opted not to hardcode credentials (a core best practice you asked for), you will need to map these exact Repository Secrets in your GitHub repository before the pipeline will run successfully.

Go to **Settings > Secrets and variables > Actions**, and ensure the following are created:
* `SONAR_TOKEN`
* `SONAR_HOST_URL`
* `SNYK_TOKEN`
* `DOCKER_USERNAME`
* `DOCKER_PASSWORD`
* `SMTP_USERNAME`
* `SMTP_PASSWORD`
* `EMAIL_RECIPIENTS` (e.g., `devops@example.com`)

Simply commit this new branch, add your variables, and you will have a robust, production-ready CI pipeline!
